Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Teen Services Librarian (Full-Time, Permanent) Cambridge , ON Description Posting #23-47x Teen Services LibrarianFull-Time, PermanentClemens Mill BranchIdea Exchange is a community hub comprised of the public libraries and art galleries for the City of Cambridge, a thriving city with a rich architectural heritage and the second largest community within the Waterloo Region. We are committed to supporting and inspiring our community in the exploration of reading, arts, innovation, and learning.As Teen Services Librarian, you will work with a team to provide information services to Idea Exchange members as well as staff and students at St. Benedict Catholic Secondary School. You will help our members learn about and navigate library and community resources, and create and implement innovative teen programming when required.What You’ll DoAs Teen Services Librarian, you will:Provide comprehensive support to library members, including answering inquiries, offering guidance on research, assisting with technology use, and managing circulation tasks.Create and maintain content for the St. Benedict CSS website in alignment with Waterloo Catholic District School Board guidelines under the direction of the Manager.Collaborate with school staff to plan and execute outreach events to promote Idea Exchange, enhancing its visibility and engagement.Deliver bibliographic instruction, curate age-appropriate resources, and develop engaging programming tailored to teen’s interests and curriculum requirements.Embrace digital resources, e-books, and online databases, staying updated on educational trends, and teach information literacy skills to students and staff.Evaluate library materials, monitor budget expenditures, and assist in addressing inappropriate behavior, while actively contributing to policy development and engaging in creative displays to promote library resources.Answer reference questions, recommend reading material, and instruct members on the use of library equipment and other new technologiesIn the absence of the Branch Manager, act as a Person-In-Charge for the building Perform daily branch activities such as registering new members and cash transactionsAssist with branch collection managementAssist with adult programming and group toursWhat You’ll Need to SucceedTo be qualified for and successful in the role, you should have:Required - University Masters in Library Information Science or Information StudiesRequired – Previous public library experience: 1 yearRequired – Experience working with youth in a work environment – 1 yearRequired – Previous experience working with the public in a service environment: 1 yearStrong communication skills and member-focused service mentality.Proficiency in website content management and digital resources.Ability to collaborate effectively with school staff and promote library initiatives.Expertise in information literacy, technology, and curriculum-based resource selection.Keen organizational skills for administrative tasksAbility to monitor budget expenditures.Creative and adaptable, with a passion for promoting library resources and programs.Ability to apply critical thinking and problem-solving skillsWhat We OfferWorking at Idea Exchange offers you the opportunity to be part of an organization that is welcoming, collaborative, and passionate about the community.We provide fair market compensation, consistent and reliable work schedules, paid sick time and free parking. We also offer participation in the OMERS pension plan.Pay: Salary range: $64,578 to $78,507 per year.Hours: 70 hours in a two-week period.Schedule: working various day, evening, and weekend shiftsThe position may require work from multiple branch locations within CambridgeThe regular schedule is as follows and is subject to change. A temporary starting schedule may be assigned.Monday to Friday 8:00am to 4:00pm*During the summer months and when St. Benedict C.S.S is closed, these hours will change to include days (9:30a.m. – 5:30 p.m.), 1 evening per week and rotational weekends.Note: schedules are service-driven and as such are subject to change.How to ApplyTo be considered for the position, please apply by November 22, 2023Tell us why we should consider you for this position! Please provide both a cover letter and resume, combined as a single PDF document.Submit your application by email to recruitment@ideaexchange.orgIf applying by email, please quote “23-47x Teen Services Librarian” in your email subject line.The anticipated start date for this position is December 2023/ January 2024The position is open to internal and external candidates. We thank everyone for their interest, however only those candidates selected for an interview will be contacted.Additional InformationIdea Exchange aspires to employ a staff complement that fully represents the diversity of the community we serve. All qualified individuals who would contribute to the further diversification of our organization are encouraged to apply.Idea Exchange is an equal opportunity employer and is committed to accommodating individual needs in accordance with the Accessibility for Ontarians with Disabilities Act (AODA). If you require any accommodations at any point during the application and hiring process, please contact Human Resources at hr@ideaexchange.org.A Security Clearance Check with Vulnerable Sector Screening will be required. Compensation $64,578 to $78,507 per year. Closes: 22 November, 2023 Idea Exchange Cambridge , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
