Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Manager of Technology and Collections SAULT STE MARIE , ON Description The Opportunity Our library is seeking a Manager of Technology and Collections to manage our Technical Services Department and to oversee our Library’s technology needs in collaboration with the City of Sault Ste. Marie’s IT Department. You will be part of our Library’s management team working together to improve library services to our local community. About SSMPL Our Library is located in beautiful Sault Ste. Marie. With a staff of approximately 50 people (full and part-time), we serve a population of over 75,000. We have two locations. Our main location is the James L. McIntyre Centennial Library. Our second location is the North Branch. Our Library has a great relationship with the municipality and many strong ties within the community. To learn more about our library please visit our website www.ssmpl.ca Why Make the Switch? Located in Northern Ontario, Sault Ste. Marie is on the border to Michigan, USA. Being surrounded by nature, our city offers an abundance of outdoor recreational activities and adventures. Have you ever dreamed of owning your own home but couldn’t because of the housing market where you live? Sault Ste. Marie has affordable housing. Moving here could make that dream come true! For more information about our city visit https://saulttourism.com/ Beside the opportunity to work with great staff, our Library offers a competitive salary and benefits package which includes a Health Care Spending account for Managers. We are also willing to provide financial assistance for relocation of the successful candidate. So if you are looking to advance your career or need a change in environment, this position might be right for you! Our Ideal Candidate We are seeking a passionate professional with a Master of Library Science or Master of Library and Information Science from an American Library Association accredited university. We will also consider someone with a combination of education in a related IT field and experience working in a public library. You should have experience related to computer hardware/software support and working knowledge of implementation and maintenance of ILS software, hardware, networks and associated web based services. Some experience supervising and training staff is ideal, but we are willing to train the successful candidate if needed. Key Competencies Include: Continuous learning Collaboration/Relationship buildingGrowth with a creative mindsetCommunicationCustomer service A full job description is available upon request. How to Apply Qualified applicants interested in this exciting and challenging opportunity should send a resume and cover letter to: Matthew MacDonald, CEO,Sault Ste. Marie Public Library50 East St.Sault Ste. Marie, ONP6A 3C3 Email: m.macdonald@cityssm.on.ca Closing Date for the first review of applications is Monday December 4, 2023 at 12:00 p.m. We will be keeping this position vacant until an appropriate candidate is found. If you have any questions please contact Matthew MacDonald, CEO, at 705-759-5246 or email: m.macdonald@cityssm.on.ca The Sault Ste. Marie Public Library in its ongoing efforts to prevent, identify and remove barriers for people with disabilities will provide work-related accommodation for employees with disabilities, upon request. Compensation $69,301 - $82,531 Closes: 4 December, 2023 Sault Ste. Marie Public Library SAULT STE MARIE , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
