 your colleagues and interact with students, faculty, and members of the community by providing referral and information services, such as locating print and digital resources, circulating materials, creating user accounts, providing printing technical support, handling payments, maintaining patron and item records, and performing opening/closing duties.CapU Library is seeking a team member who:is curious/inquisitivetakes responsibility for their workenjoys working with people of diverse backgrounds and perspectivescommunicates effectively in groups and one-on-oneis a critical thinkeris able to interpret automated catalogue recordsis able to communicate complex technical information clearlydemonstrates data literacy as required by the positionis thorough and accurate in their work and has a high level of attention to detailThe applicant should have experience with:Information organization and retrieval in a library environmentIntegrated Library Systems (ILS) – (Capilano University Library uses Sierra)Microsoft Office (Excel, Word, Outlook, &amp; PowerPoint)What you’ll bringCompletion of a two-year Library Technology diploma comparable to the programs offered at Langara College or University of the Fraser Valley.Two years of library technical services, cataloguing, ILL, or other related experience.For more informationFor more information, please see the complete job description.BenefitsAt Capilano University, we understand that there is more to life than work. That is why we offer comprehensive benefits and support to help you and your family live a balanced life. Take a sneak peak to see what it is like to work at Capilano University.Posting Detail InformationDays and Hours of WorkOur standard work week is Monday to Friday, 8:30am – 4:00pm.Bridge Period (if applicable)Pay Group16Salary$52,716 annually based on 35 hours per week (with increments up to $59,256)UnionMoveUPJob Open Date11/06/2023Job Close Date11/20/2023Open Until FilledNoQuick Link for Postinghttps://jo