Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? 2023-12 - Library Technician (RPT, 22 hours/week) North Vancouver , BC Description North Vancouver City Library is seeking an enthusiastic, adaptable and technologically savvy Library Technician to join our team part-time (22 hours per week).As part of the Information &amp; Reader Services team, you will be responsible for providing information and reader’s advisory services for all ages and audiences, as well as in-depth public technology support and group technology instruction.The successful candidate for this position will demonstrate: The ability to prepare and deliver effective one-to-one and group public technology support and instruction for a variety of ages and audiences; Strong general technology skills; and The ability to support the public in learning, using and troubleshooting digitization and audio/video recording software and equipment.In addition, the successful candidate will be able to provide a range of library public services for all ages and audiences, including information and reader’s advisory services, programming and outreach, and collection management activities. A commitment to customer service rooted in equity and respect is essential.If you are passionate about providing exceptional customer service and creative programming, and if you enjoy being part of a dynamic team, then we would love to hear from you!Please refer to the attached Job Classification Specification for further details.QualificationsCompletion of an approved Library Technician diploma program including relevant courses, plus some customer service or library experience, or an equivalent combination of relevant training and experience.The ability to appropriately incorporate Indigenous ways of knowing into programs or to deliver programs and services in a language other than English would be an asset.Apply to: Deb Hutchison Koep, Chief Librarianhttps://www.nvcl.ca/about#jobsNote: When uploading documents to your profile, the maximum size allowed per document is 1MB. Please ensure the document file name and file extension is all lower case (i.e. .pdf and not .PDF). If you are having difficulty attaching documents, please click on the “question mark” icon on the top right side of the screen for technical support.Start Date: December 4, 2023Salary: $27.43 - $32.23/hour (pay grade 16; 2021 rates) + 10%Schedule:Sunday – 1 – 5 p.m.Monday – 9:30 a.m. – 5 p.m.Tuesday – 4 – 8 p.m.Thursday – 9:30 a.m. – 5 p.m.Schedules are reviewed periodically and subject to change. Evening and weekend work may be required.Closing Date: November 19, 2023 at 5 p.m. PSTNorth Vancouver City Library is committed to recruiting and hiring candidates that reflect the community we serve. We welcome applicants from diverse backgrounds, including Indigenous candidates, all identities, candidates who speak languages in addition to English, and persons with disabilities.Accommodations are available on request for candidates in all parts of the selection process.About us:The North Vancouver City Library is located in the heart of the City of North Vancouver. As a valued public service, our library is a centre for discovery and dialogue, providing a gateway to lifelong learning and community connection through a balance of digital, traditional and emerging library services. Our decision-making is guided by deeply held values: https://www.nvcl.ca/about/mission Compensation $27.43 – $32.23/hour (pay grade 16; 2021 rates), plus 10% in lieu of benefits Closes: 19 November, 2023 North Vancouver City Library North Vancouver , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
