Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Acquisitions &amp; Metadata Assistant, Library Acquisitions Unit Winnipeg , MB Description Competition Number: A126.23Classification: Library Assistant 4Department: LibraryEmployee Group: AESESPosition Category: Full-Time, ContinuingHours: 35 hours per weekFunding: BudgetStart Date: As soon as possibleLocation: Winnipeg, MBJob Type: ContinuingStatus: ExistingDate Posted: 10/31/2023Closing Date: 11/14/2023Salary Range: $40,276.60 - $55,546.40The mission of the Library is to provide and organize resources necessary to effectively support teaching, and research at The University of Winnipeg.The Acquisitions &amp; Metadata Assistant is a full-time continuing position that provides resource acquisitions and metadata support for the Library. In Acquisitions, this position is responsible for creating order records, entering encumbrances, tracking orders, and aiding with the payment of invoices. In Metadata, this position is responsible for creating and updating records for library resources.Responsibilities:Prepares, processes and tracks orders for digital and physical Library resources by: identifying vendor/access options, creating order records, entering encumbrances, receiving new resources, paying invoices, and liaising with vendors, faculty, and staff. Determines availability and best vendor/supplier option for print book, eBook, and video orders.Uses the Integrated Library System to create order records, make payments, and pay invoices.Works with the Acquisitions Supervisor ensuring orders are processed and encumbered in an appropriate fashion, and that materials are received at the appropriate time.Places claims for materials not received or not properly received.Monitors expenditure records for departmental book budgets, and regularly reports budget information to subject librarians.Uses various resource management systems to create, derive, modify, and update records describing the library’s digital and physical resources.Performs title reconciliations, creates new database records, activates or deactivate titles and/or collections, updates licensing and proxy information, etc.Ensures digital collection title lists are accurate, and that resource links are working.Performs original and copy cataloguing in MARC and non-MARC formats, using appropriate standards and vocabularies like RDA, LCC, LCSH, Homosaurus, and more.Collaborates with colleagues to address bias in our institution’s metadata, and to create more inclusive descriptions of our resources.Uses automated or manual procedures to modify, update, or activate records describing Library resources.Performs initial troubleshooting on digital resource record and access issues.Tracks reported digital resource issues from beginning to end.Participates in developing and maintaining policies, procedures and manuals for Acquisitions, Metadata, and digital resource troubleshooting.Attends meetings and takes part in Library committees as appropriate.Qualifications:2-year diploma from a recognized Library technician’s program (or equivalent).Undergraduate degree would be an asset.Directly related library experience, using procedures and systems appropriate to the area.Experience with ordering, receiving, and paying invoices for resources.Experience with descriptive metadata work, using standards and vocabularies such as RDA, MARC 21, KBART, LCC and LCSH.Experience with Microsoft Outlook and Microsoft 365.Attention to detail.Ability to understand and follow oral and written instructions.Ability to work independently and cooperatively with others.Ability to communicate effectively with faculty, staff, and vendor/publishers.Working understanding of knowledge bases and/or related tools.Demonstrated problem solving and critical thinking skills.Demonstrated initiative to learn new technologies and software. An equivalent combination of education, experience, skills, knowledge and abilities may be considered. Condition(s) of Employment:Must be legally entitled to work in Canada.The salary range for this position will be from $40,276.60 to $55,546.40 annually.Note: The work described in this posting will be conducted in-person.The University of Winnipeg is committed to equity, diversity and inclusion and recognizes that a diverse staff and faculty benefits and enriches the work, learning and research environments, and is essential to academic and institutional excellence. We welcome applications from all qualified individuals and encourage women, racialized persons, Indigenous persons, persons with disabilities, and 2SLGBTQ+ persons to confidentially self-identify at time of application.The University of Winnipeg is committed to ensuring employment opportunities are accessible for all applicants. If you require accommodation supports during the recruitment process, please contact human_resources@uwinnipeg.ca.The personal information of applicants is collected under the authority of the University of Winnipeg Act and 36(1)(b) of the Freedom of Information and Protection of Privacy Act. All personal information collected via the recruitment process is used to assess the applicant’s suitability, eligibility, and qualifications for employment, and to otherwise support recruitment activities. This information will be provided to participating members of the recruitment process. Questions regarding the collection of your personal information may be directed to the Director, HR Services, 515 Portage Avenue, Winnipeg, MB, R3B 2E9 or human_resources@uwinnipeg.ca.To apply: Login - University of Winnipeg (northstarats.com) Compensation $40,276.60 - $55,546.40 Closes: 14 November, 2023 University of Winnipeg Winnipeg , MB Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
