Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Branch Head - Mobile Library Kamloops , BC Description About the Thompson-Nicola Regional DistrictEncompassing an unparalleled geographic region in the heart of British Columbia, the Thompson-Nicola Regional District (TNRD) offers the best of both worlds. Urban life within vibrant communities and outlying rural regions showcase the region's beauty: pristine but rugged mountains, rolling grasslands, lush evergreen forests and both historic and modern areas, all within approximately 45,000 square kilometres. Headquartered in the City of Kamloops, the TNRD provides a wide range of local government services to a population of 151,086 located within its 11 diverse municipalities and 10 electoral areas.Kamloops is situated on the traditional and unceded lands of the Tk’emlúps te Secwepemc within Secwepemc’ulucw territory at the confluence of the mighty North and South Thompson rivers. A mecca for sports and outdoor enthusiasts, Canada’s Tournament Capital City is located 350 km from Vancouver and a short 45-minute drive from the resort Village of Sun Peaks Resort known for its world-class ski runs, hiking rails and bike park. Minutes away from pristine lakes and wildlife, it’s not unusual to encounter deer, coyotes, or bears in this supernatural BC territory. Let your imagination run wild!Our Library System and the Mobile LibraryThe Thompson-Nicola Regional Library (TNRL), the largest department of the Regional District provides services through 12 locations and a Mobile Library. Located in the Central Interior of British Columbia, the TNRL is committed to providing excellent service to patrons for lifetime personal growth, learning and enjoyment. The Library team provides programming, materials and resources to people of all backgrounds, ages and abilities. As a member of the TNRL, you will help to build strong relationships and partnerships in all our communities.The Mobile Library is a 2018 retrofitted 36’ International five-ton truck, with a mounted custom-built box with three slides and a generator housing a full-service library providing a range of materials including books, magazines, DVDs and more. The ML offers regular service to 30 rural and urban locations across the regional district. Patrons also visit the Mobile Library to use its public Wi-Fi and receive technology support. This award-winning vehicle also serves as a large Library billboard!The RoleThe TNRL is recruiting a Temporary Branch Head for the Mobile Library, who is eager to work in a vibrant public library. The Temporary Branch Head will work in an organization that values flexibility, customer service and making a difference in our communities as we strive to build partnerships within and outside the library system. The Temporary Branch Head will help patrons of all ages with circulation, reference, readers’ advisory and technology questions. The Temporary Branch Head will lead and organize the department, prioritize tasks and resources, deliver via the Mobile Library or other fleet vehicles, and offer library services to communities across the regional district. Other duties include staff scheduling, payroll approval, promotion, troubleshooting minor repairs or scheduling regular maintenance, collection management, as well as performing routine tasks that require heavy lifting, pushing and pulling, and keeping the Mobile Library looking its very best! The Temporary Branch Head will develop and maintain effective relationships with staff, patrons and the community; be a team player with excellent interpersonal and communication skills; and have a working understanding of emerging trends, technologies, and best practices in public library services and ingenuity to adopt them to a mobile service. Working collegially with other branch heads and coordinators, the Temporary Branch Head will participate in meetings and system-wide projects for the betterment of services across the TNRL. Attending meetings, and working collegially with other TNRD departments such as Payroll, Finance and Facilities, are all required. No day is routine for the Temporary Branch Head. Interactions will constantly challenge and inspire you to position the library as an exciting hub in the community. You will support the training and development of a small but dedicated staff team, building their strengths to ensure that the TNRL's excellent customer service standards are maintained.The Temporary Branch Head is tasked with launching a number of new stops in 2024 and ensuring their success. The Temporary Branch Head will need to be responsive to community feedback, assist with hiring, and the training and support of new staff or casuals. JOB REQUIREMENTSThe Ideal Candidate will have:Completion of a Diploma or other 2-year college/university program.A valid class 5 BC driver’s license with On-highway Air Brake Endorsement and a clean driver’s abstract.Minimum 2 years’ experience driving a large single-axle vehicle with air brake capabilities in all weather conditions.Completion of a children’s literature course from a recognized college or university or completed the CLTP Children and Young Adult courses (or equivalent).Additional Assets:Leadership experience with the capability to inspire employeesA passion for helping others and a belief in the importance of literacyAbility to build strong connections to the communitiesDemonstrated respect and concern for others, open-mindedness and generosity of spiritA good sense of humourA commitment to equity, diversity and inclusion, understanding that the public library is for everyone!Experience working with children (other than one's own) in a professional capacity. For example, experience as a teacher, daycare worker or sports coach.Experience designing and delivering children’s programs.Mechanical aptitude – the ability to effectively monitor vehicle performance and mechanical fitness via pre- and post-trip inspections.Strong physical ability including standing or walking for an entire work day, heavy pushing, pulling, lifting or carrying, chaining up and snow shovelling as needed, and seated for extended periods during driving. Must be able to work in environmental conditions that may include exposure to dust, dirt, heat, cold, noise, fumes, odours, vibrations, humidity and temperature changes.Excellent oral, written, and interpersonal skills.Demonstrated ability to multi-task and work under pressure within tight deadlines and regular interruptions.Ability to work independently and as part of a team.An aptitude for technology. This includes:Understanding of Windows, Android and iOS operating systems and familiarity with Microsoft Office programs.Minimum keyboarding speed of 35wpm.Ability to troubleshoot peripheral equipment such as printers, USB drives and wireless internet connections.Ability to work with and learn a variety of software applications independently.Ability to assist patrons with e-readers, tablets, smartphones, social media, email and eBooks/audiobooks.Take responsibility for the safety of the vehicle, staff, and the public during emergency situations, including threatening weather and vehicle trouble.Prep, inspect, and drive the Mobile Library safely and promptly to scheduled daily stops and special events.Provide additional outreach services, such as stops to care homes, school visits, community events and other emergent solutions to extend the library’s reach.Posting DetailsThis Temporary Full-Time position is subject to the provisions of the Collective Agreement with the BC General Employees' Union, local 705. The TNRL requires that all successful applicants undergo a Criminal Record Check. The Temporary Branch Head is a Grid 14 (pay rate $29.38-$32.58 per hour). Non-benefitted staff receive a percentage in lieu of benefits. A Sunday premium also applies at $1.50 per hour. The temporary full-time position is expected to begin in December of 2023 and end in December of 2024. This temporary position may be shortened or extended with 7 days' notice. The Temporary Branch Head will work weekends (Saturday and Sundays, evenings and overnight) and also Work Alone. The work schedule rotates to ensure the Temporary Branch Head works all routes and shifts during the year. Flexibility is required as the operation needs. The Mobile Library operates in all weather conditions. Apply with your cover letter and resume today! Careers - Thompson-Nicola Regional District (tnrd.ca) Compensation $29.38 - $32.58 Closes: 17 November, 2023 Thompson-Nicola Regional Library Kamloops , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
