Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Assistant librarian – Collections / Adult services Hanover , ON Description The Hanover Public Library in Ontario is seeking an Assistant Librarian to join our team. As a busy library serving the rural town of Hanover in the Grey Bruce area, we are looking for a candidate who is passionate about collection development and engaging with the community. You will work with a friendly and supportive team providing excellent public library services. Your role includes purchasing or borrowing materials, cataloguing, organizing and marketing the collection, all to help people discover their next great read. Our single site library offers flexible shifts, staff input to strategic direction and events, a variety of duties and a friendly team. This position can be full time (Assistant Librarian – Adult Services with adult programming) or part time (Assistant Librarian – Collections, 21-28 hours/week). OMERS pension plan and other benefits available. Responsibilities Develop and maintain the library's adult collection, including selecting and purchasing materials, and weeding outdated or damaged itemsManage the collections budgetCreate and maintain MARC catalogue records in automated library systemManage interlibrary loans, including processing requests, tracking materials, and maintaining accurate recordsProvide circulation, reference, research and technical assistance to library patrons, including readers’ advisory and support for the public using computers and the InternetPlan and implement library programs and events, including author visits, book clubs, and workshops (full-time position only)Stay up-to-date with current trends and best practices in library services and technology Requirements Post-secondary education such as a Masters in Library Science is an asset or Library and Information Technician DiplomaCompletion of a certified course in library cataloguing, such as ALA Fundamentals of Cataloguing or within credits for academic qualificationMinimum four (4) years’ experience working in public library servicesMinimum three (3) years working in reader advisory and collection management rolesHas thorough knowledge of public library operation and managementHas experience managing budgets, analyzing library collection usage, planning and performing collection developmentIs familiar with automated Integrated Library Management and Interlibrary Loans systems Has experience creating and managing catalogue records in an automated systemStrong customer service skills and ability to assess and guide people’s reading developmentExcellent communication and interpersonal skillsConsiderable knowledge of collection development practices and tools, publishing industry, library materials, authors, resources and trends Experience creating and running programming/events for adults in a library or relatable context (full-time position only)The Library will require a current Vulnerable Sector Screening from the successful applicantWe will review applications on a rolling basis until the position is filled, so don't delay! Please see full job descriptions and how to apply for the Full time or Part time positions here: https://hanoverlibrary.ca/uncategorized/job-opport... Compensation $26.44/hr to $30.74/hr, Salary Grid, Group 8 Closes: 16 January, 2024 Hanover Public Library Hanover , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
