of duties relating to the job. Effectively communicate and interact with staff in a professional and respectful manner, establish and maintain effective working relationships, with supervisors, members of the general public and all other groups involved in the activities of the library. Assemble information and make written reports and documents in a concise, clear, and effective manner. Use independent judgment and work with little direct supervision when necessary. Must learn and use the library computer system, hardware, and specialized software with high degree of efficiency. Excellent written and oral communication skills. Hourly wage: $22.37 - $29.36 plus vacation pay, pension and benefits. Position is 35 hours per week.Please submit cover letter and resume to:Mary C. Moore Public Librarymcmpl@prl.ab.ca by emailor can be dropped off in person at:101-5214 50th Avenue Lacombe, Alberta T4L 0B6 No phone calls please. You will only be contacted if you are granted an interview for the position.Position will remain open until a suitable candidate is found. Compensation $22.37 - $29.36 Closes: 20 December, 2023 Mary C. Moore Public Library Lacombe , AB Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
